OPTION A: Running setup_database.py

Edit setup_database.py username to match a kilter board account. An account must be created through the mobile app here:
https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.auroraclimbing.kilterboard

Afterwards, run the setup_database file to download the database. If prompted to enter a password, enter the password for
your kilterboard account.


OPTION B: Downloading through terminal

Step 0: An account must be created through the mobile app here:
https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.auroraclimbing.kilterboard

Step 1: Clone the BoardLib github repo by running the following line in the terminal:
git clone https://github.com/lemeryfertitta/BoardLib.git

Step 2: Download the database using the following line
python -m boardlib database kilter kilter_board.db --username <input_kilterboard_username>

Step 3: User will be prompted to enter a password to sync the database, enter your password for you kilter board account.


FINAL:

After either Option A or B are complete, run extract_routes.py to extract the data from the database into a .csv file.